# =============================================================================
# File: /opt/ansible-k3s-cluster/README.cluster-governance-model
# =============================================================================
# Purpose:
#   Define the governance model for the cluster automation framework. This
#   ensures consistent decision-making, safe operations, and clear authority.
#
# Governance Components:
#
#   1. Roles & Responsibilities
#      - Builder: kernel creation
#      - Ansible: deployment & diagnostics
#      - Nodes: execution & reporting
#
#   2. Change Control
#      - Kernel changes require verification + audit log
#      - Deployment requires preflight checks
#
#   3. Risk Management
#      - Rollback-first philosophy
#      - Immutable artifacts
#
#   4. Documentation Standards
#      - ASCII-safe
#      - nano-safe
#      - Fully reproducible
#
# Notes:
#   - This file defines the authoritative governance model.
# =============================================================================
